FBIS4-63234 "drsov098_e_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Black Sea Fleet Only To Take Orders From Kravchuk, Yeltsin Black Sea Fleet Only To Take Orders From Kravchuk, Yeltsin LD1905174994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1616 GMT 19 May 94 LD1905174994 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Commander of the Black Sea Fleet Admiral Eduard Baltin met with Deputy-Chairman of the Ukrainian National Security Service Oleg Pugach in Sevastopol on Thursday [19 May] to discuss the situation in Crimea, sources in the Black Sea Fleet's headquarters told INTERFAX. Baltin confirmed that the Black Sea Fleet Commanders would not fulfill any orders except the ones coming from the Russian and Ukrainian presidents.
